 <body>

  <div class="explanation">

   <h2><a href="http://www.unto.net/">Unto.net</a> &gt; <a href="$site_info.project_url">Delancey</a> &gt; $username &gt; Claim &gt; Verify</h2>

   <p>
    These forms will allow you to claim the del.icio.us username
    <strong>$username</strong> on Delancey.
   </p>

  </div>

  <div class="tasks">

   <h3>Steps:</h3>

   <p>Folow these three steps to claim <strong>$username</strong> as your Delancey username.</p>

   <div class="completed-task task">
    <p><h4>Step 1:</h4> Choose a Delancey password.  Completed.</p>
   </div>

   <div class="active-task task">
    <p><h4>&raquo; Step 2:</h4> Please verify your del.icio.us username by clicking on the following link:</p>

    <form id="verify-password" method="post" action="http://del.icio.us/$username/">
     <input type="hidden" name="url" value="$claim_url"/>
     <input type="hidden" name="oldurl" value="$claim_url"/>
     <input type="hidden" name="description" value="$username's Delancey claim"/>
     <input type="hidden" name="notes" value="Click to complete your Delancey claim."/>
     <input id="verify-password-submit" class="form-submit" type="submit" value="Verify your del.icio.us username"/> 
    </form>

    <p>Note that you must be <a href="http://del.icio.us/login">logged
     in to del.icio.us</a> for this to work automatically. If it fails, either log in and try again, or hit "save" by hand and follow the bookmark.</p>
   </div>

   <div class="disabled-task task">
    <p><h4>Step 3:</h4> Complete the claim.</p>
   </div>
  
  </div>


  <div class="explanation">

   <h3>Explanation:</h3>

   <p>
    You are about to stake a claim on the username
    <strong>$username</strong> at Delancey.  This means that you, and
    only you, can update Delancey information using the username
    <strong>$username</strong>.  But first, you are required to
    demonstrate that you are
    <strong>$username</strong> at del.icio.us.
   </p>

   <p>
    This process has three steps.  First, you will choose a Delancey
    password and send it to the Delancey servers. This password should
    not be the same as your del.icio.us password.
   </p>

   <p>
    Second, you will need need to prove to the Delancey server that
    you are <strong>$username</strong> at del.icio.us.  You will do
    this by using del.icio.us to bookmark a unique URL for the 
    Delancey server to read.
   </p>

   <p>
    Third, you can complete your claim
    <strong>$username</strong> on Delancey.  If you ever need to
    reset your password, just return to <a
    href="$site_info.project_url/claim/choose/$username">the claim
    page</a> and try again.
   </p>

  </div>

